<p>President Trump publicly urged Senate Republicans to invoke the &quot;nuclear option&quot; — a rule change to remove the 60-vote cloture threshold — to break what he called a Democratic roadblock and force an end to the ongoing US government shutdown . His push would let most legislation, including funding measures, advance on a simple majority instead of the traditional 60-vote requirement . The appeal comes as the shutdown drags on toward matching the previous record and is putting pressure on congressional Republicans to deliver a resolution quickly .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/VBvRJ9RmvAemu8wSkhhlAb6tP0S_5gDM5qpZ2Dg5OOUD1ScJmapwDhH_KB29sOnyRb_syMTCsJo-tb2AdW6sdkfbPAT5-gwgFsHeAyRmWWPIYvdV9WVw0m-_2bpZGWSdqyUmcAK53rB4jgnrsjL-ZjDlzZq5UfmqtEVeQ4ZwIXPcZH4eKg6YKjMxFFC9yQfL' alt='Representational image accompanying coverage of President Trump&#x27;s call to use the &#x27;nuclear option&#x27;' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Senate arithmetic: Republicans currently hold a 53-47 Senate majority and a 219-213 majority in the House, framing how quickly a rules change could be politically feasible .</li><li>SNAP urgency: Federal food assistance faces a near-term disruption: SNAP benefits are set to lapse this weekend and a judge has signaled she may order reserves used to partially fund assistance for roughly 42 million Americans in November .</li><li>Retail impact: U.S. grocers and food companies, including major chains named in reporting, are preparing for a sales dip in November if federal food benefits lapse for the first time during this shutdown .</li><li>Political pressure: Republicans are under mounting pressure from their own White House and some party quarters to act quickly to end the shutdown, prompting renewed debate over changing Senate norms .</li></ul><blockquote>It is time to get rid of U.S. Senate&#x27;s filibuster custom - President Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Trump: He urged Senate Republicans to use the &#x27;nuclear option&#x27; to remove the 60-vote hurdle so funding and other measures can pass on a simple majority . (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/use-the-nuclear-option-trump-tells-senate-republicans-how-to-end-govt-shutdown-13946739.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Federal judge (court proceeding): A federal judge has indicated she could order the administration to use reserve funds to partially continue food assistance for about 42 million Americans in November if Congress does not act . (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2025/oct/31/donald-trump-filibuster-shutdown-snap-food-refugees-drug-boats-latest-news-updates'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>U.S. grocers and food companies: Retailers and food producers say a lapse in federal benefits could reduce November spending at stores, and several companies are publicly bracing for that shortfall . (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2025/oct/31/donald-trump-filibuster-shutdown-snap-food-refugees-drug-boats-latest-news-updates'>The Guardian</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/use-the-nuclear-option-trump-tells-senate-republicans-how-to-end-govt-shutdown-13946739.html'>‘Use the nuclear option’: Trump tells Senate Republicans how to end govt shutdown</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/us-president-donald-trump-urges-senate-to-scrap-60-vote-rule-as-shutdown-drags-on-9549726#publisher=newsstand'>Trump Urges Senate To Scrap 60-Vote Rule As Shutdown Drags On</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/trump-says-it-is-time-to-get-rid-of-us-senates-filibuster-custom/article70224146.ece'>Trump says it is time to get rid of U.S. Senate&#x27;s filibuster custom</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/united-states/trump-calls-for-us-senate-to-scrap-filibuster-rule'>Trump calls for US Senate to scrap filibuster rule</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='htt